ne"},{"children":[],"comments":"Check if we're still in the warmup phase (uses < operator).\n\nDuring warmup, the algorithm explores more aggressively.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Boolean"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[309,39],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Online/Algorithm.purs","start":[309,1]},"title":"isWarmupPhase"},{"children":[],"comments":"Get the dimension of a ground set (uses dim).\n\nCreates a new Dim from the ground set's internal size for comparison operations.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":{"identifier":"v","kind":null,"skolem":null,"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","GroundSet"],"GroundSet"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Tensor","Dimension"],"Dim"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},"visibility":"TypeVarInvisible"},"tag":"ForAll"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[315,51],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Online/Algorithm.purs","start":[315,1]},"title":"groundSetDimension"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create a fractional solution from coordinate map (uses mkFractionalSolution).\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":{"identifier":"v","kind":null,"skolem":null,"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","GroundSet"],"GroundSet"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Map","Internal"],"Map"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Continuous","FractionalSolution"],"FractionalSolution"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},"visibility":"TypeVarInvisible"},"tag":"ForAll"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[321,86],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Online/Algorithm.purs","start":[321,1]},"title":"solutionFromCoords"},{"children":[],"comments":"Get a coordinate from a fractional solution (uses solutionCoord).\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":{"identifier":"v","kind":null,"skolem":null,"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Continuous","FractionalSolution"],"FractionalSolution"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","GroundSet"],"Element"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},"visibility":"TypeVarInvisible"},"tag":"ForAll"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[325,74],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Online/Algorithm.purs","start":[325,1]},"title":"getSolutionCoord"},{"children":[],"comments":"Extract ground set size from a fractional solution.\n\n## Lean Correspondence\n\nThis function corresponds to `Fintype.card V` in the Lean proofs.\n\nIn Lean (`Core.lean:232`):\n```lean\nstructure FractionalSolution (V : Type*) where\n  coords : V → ℝ\n  nonneg : ∀ v, 0 ≤ coords v\n  le_one : ∀ v, coords v ≤ 1\n```\n\nThe PureScript representation stores `groundSetSize :: Int` explicitly because\nwe use index-based elements (`Element v = Element Int`) rather than type-level\nground sets. This corresponds to `Fintype.card V` in theorems like:\n\n- `matroidRank_le_card` (Matroid.lean:259): `matroidRank M ≤ Fintype.card V`\n- `wtp_matroid_raoco` (RAOCO.lean:369): `Fintype.card V = n`\n\n## Usage\n\nUsed to verify solution dimensions match polytope constraints:\n- RAOCO reduction requires solutions to have correct dimension\n- Regret bounds depend on n = |V| (ground set size)\n\n## Pattern Match Justification\n\nPattern matches on `FractionalSolution` constructor to access internal state.\nThis is necessary because `FractionalSolution` is a newtype wrapping a record.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":{"identifier":"v","kind":null,"skolem":null,"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Continuous","FractionalSolution"],"FractionalSolution"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},"visibility":"TypeVarInvisible"},"tag":"ForAll"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[363,63],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Online/Algorithm.purs","start":[363,1]},"title":"solutionGroundSetSize"},{"children":[],"comments":"Extract ground set from matroid polytope.\n\n## Lean Correspondence\n\nThis function provides access to the ground set V over which the matroid\npolytope is defined. In Lean (`Matroid.lean:155`):\n\n```lean\ndef inPolytope (M : Matroid V) (x : V → ℝ) : Prop :=\n  (∀ v, 0 ≤ x v) ∧ \n  (∀ v, x v ≤ 1) ∧\n  (∀ S : Finset V, S.sum x ≤ rank M S)\n```\n\nThe ground set V is implicit in Lean but must be explicit in PureScript.\nThis accessor enables iteration over elements for:\n\n- Computing threshold potentials (`RAOCO.lean:110`):\n  `thresholdPotential b w S x = min b (S.sum fun v => if v ∈ x then w v else 0)`\n\n- Gradient computation (`ContinuousGreedy.lean:87`):\n  `gradient_lower_bound` requires summing over elements in V\n\n- Sandwich property verification (`RAOCO.lean:178`):\n  Requires evaluating rank constraints for all S ⊆ V\n\n## Pattern Match Justification\n\nPattern matches on `MatroidPolytope` constructor to access the wrapped\nmatroid and ground set. The ground set is needed for:\n1. Enumerating elements during linear optimization\n2. Constructing indicator vectors for independent sets\n3. Computing the multilinear extension via sampling\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":{"identifier":"m","kind":null,"skolem":null,"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":{"identifier":"v","kind":null,"skolem":null,"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Continuous","MatroidPolytope"],"MatroidPolytope"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"m","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","GroundSet"],"GroundSet"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"v","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},"visibility":"TypeVarInvisible"},"tag":"ForAll"},"visibility":"TypeVarInvisible"},"tag":"ForAll"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[399,68],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Online/Algorithm.purs","start":[399,1]},"title":"polytopeGroundSet"}],"name":"Hydrogen.Optimize.Submodular.Online.Algorithm","reExports":[]}